						<summary>

						<p>This damaged inscription records the apportionment of taxes between the temples of Avināsi-āṇḍār and Tirumurugaṉpūṇḍi-mahādēvar. It also records that ten <hi rend="italic">achchu</hi> had been deposited for providing food offerings to the god at Tirumurugaṉpūṇḍi.</p>						

						</summary>
